<title>FRANCE: Cr Lyonnais bailout to cost 50 bln Ffr.</title>
<headline>Cr Lyonnais bailout to cost 50 bln Ffr.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-02-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>French Finance Minister Jean Arthuis said on Friday the total cost to put ailing state-owned bank Credit Lyonnais back on its feet would be more than 50 billion francs.</p>
<p>&quot;We will better know the precise degree of the disaster once the doubtful assets transferred to the Consortium de Realisation have been sold but it will be very expensive and it's a disgrace,&quot; Arthuis said in a radio interview.</p>
<p>&quot;It will be well above 50 billion francs.&quot;</p>
<p>In response to another question, Arthuis said the total debt of French public companies was about 600 billion francs.</p>
<p>Private analysts' estimates have put the cost of the state's bailouts of the bank as high 100 billion.</p>
